# Navigation

Kiroku uses React Navigation. Three files define the navigation structure:

| File | Purpose |
|---|---|
| `src/SCREENS.ts` | Screen name constants |
| `src/ROUTES.ts` | Route path definitions and builder functions |
| `src/NAVIGATORS.ts` | Navigator type constants |

## Adding a New Screen

1. Add the screen name constant to `src/SCREENS.ts` first.
2. Add the route definition (and a `getRoute` builder if it takes params) to `src/ROUTES.ts`, following the existing pattern.
3. Register the screen in the appropriate navigator component.
4. Never hardcode route strings — always reference `ROUTES.*` and `SCREENS.*`.

## Navigating

```tsx
import Navigation from '@libs/Navigation/Navigation';
import ROUTES from '@src/ROUTES';

// Navigate to a screen
Navigation.navigate(ROUTES.SOME_SCREEN);

// Navigate with params
Navigation.navigate(ROUTES.SOME_SCREEN_WITH_PARAM.getRoute(paramValue));
```

